## Central Idea: Sophistication Overrated Hai — Attackers Ke Liye

Report ka opening line hi sab kuch keh deta hai:

> *"Attackers no longer need to break in if they can simply log in."*

Zero-day exploits expensive hote hain develop karne mein. Custom malware detectable hoti hai. Kisi user ko phish karke ek legitimate remote access tool install karwana? Almost free. Aur kaam karta hai.

Blackpoint SOC ne thousands of incidents mein ek clear pattern observe kiya — adversaries ne custom hacking tools abandon kiye aur woh tools use karne lage jo organizations khud already trust karti hain. VPNs, RMM software, software installers, browser prompts — sab weaponize ho gaye. Tode nahi. **Repurpose kiye gaye.**

Report isko kehti hai **"Trusted Compromise"** — aur yahi theme har case study mein repeat hoti hai.

