## Vulnerability Landscape: Tumhara Code Is Mein Kahan Hai

45,000+ CVEs 2025 mein. Top CWE categories jo attacker-prioritized vulnerabilities drive karti hain:

|                   CWE             | % of Notifications |               Developer Translation              |
|-----------------------------------|--------------------|--------------------------------------------------|
| Deserialization of Untrusted Data |        7.3%        | User-controlled input kabhi deserialize mat karo |
| Path Traversal                    |        7.3%        | User-provided file paths pe kabhi trust mat karo |
| Use After Free                    |        6.8%        | Memory safety (mostly C/C++)                     |
| Authentication Bypass             |        5.3%        |  Server-side auth checks — always                |
| Improper Privilege Management     |        4.9%        | Principle of least privilege                     |

Top five mein se teen **application-level vulnerabilities** hain — woh jo developers code mein introduce karte hain. Network misconfiguration nahi. Outdated hardware nahi. **Code.**

### CVE Chaining: The Real Problem

Report ka sabse important vulnerability insight:

> *"Individual CVEs ko alag alag patch karna modern attack chains ke against sufficient nahi raha."*

**Gladinet CentreStack example:**

- CVE-2025-11371 (LFI, CVSS 6.1) → authenticated file reads possible → machine keys leak ho sakti hain
- CVE-2025-14611 (Hardcoded crypto keys, CVSS 7.1) → stolen machine keys se ViewState forge karo → RCE

Dono medium-severity CVEs. Individually? Limited impact. **Chain karo? Full server compromise.**

Developer lesson: **System level pe threat model karo, individual function level pe nahi.** Endpoint A mein information disclosure + Endpoint B mein logic flaw = real attack path.

